<!DOCTYPE html>

<head>
    <title>Registration Tutorial</title>
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="../style/menustyle.css">
    <link href="https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/bootstrap@5.0.0-beta3/dist/css/bootstrap.min.css" rel="stylesheet"
        integrity="sha384-eOJMYsd53ii+scO/bJGFsiCZc+5NDVN2yr8+0RDqr0Ql0h+rP48ckxlpbzKgwra6" crossorigin="anonymous">
    <script src="https://code.jquery.com/jquery-3.6.0.min.js"
        integrity="sha256-/xUj+3OJU5yExlq6GSYGSHk7tPXikynS7ogEvDej/m4=" crossorigin="anonymous"></script>
</head>

<body>
    <nav class="mainnav">
        <h3 id="player-username">{{username}}</h3>
        <ul>
            <li><a href="/">Back to Main Menu</a></li>
        </ul>
    </nav>

    <div class="main-container row mt-5 justify-content-center">

        <div class="card" style="width: 60rem">
            <h2 class="card-title  text-center">Registration Tutorial</h2>
            <div class="card-body">
                <p>When you click on the "Sign-Up" button, you will be redirected to the Registration
                    Page.</p>
                <p>Here, players are required to enter
                <ul>
                    <li>A username they will play the game with</li>
                    <li>The e-mail address they would like to use for their account</li>
                    <li>A password for the account</li>
                    <li>The password again, to make sure they remember exactly what they typed in before</li>
                </ul>

                <img class="justify-content-center" src="../img/RegistrationPageImage.jpg" alt="registration-tutorial">
                <p>1. The "Username" field. If it has already been registered in the system, you will be alerted.</p>
                <p>2. The "E-mail address" field. You must use the e-mail format(e.g. jam@gmail.com,
                    Jerry2@hotmail.com).</p>
                <p>3. The "Password" field. The password must be at least 8 characters long.</p>
                <p>4. The "Confirm Password" field. The password here must match the password previously inputted.</p>
                <p>5. The "Submit" button. You press this in order for your details to be registered.</p>
                <br>
                <p>If all details are valid and the user does not exist on the system, the account will be registered and you can log into it to play the game and have your scores saved</p>
                <br>

                <div class="d-flex justify-content-between">
                    <a class="btn btn-outline-info" href="/tutorial">About the website</a>
                    <a class="btn btn-outline-info" href="/tutorial3">Login Page</a>
                </div>


            </div>
        </div>

    </div>

</body>

</html>